        "header": "4Further Analysis",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.23166/2602.23166v2/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:Tool-use distribution across models. GPT models rely more on the code interpreter, while Gemini and Claude models use web search most frequently.",
                "position": 959
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.23166/2602.23166v2/x6.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Image manipulation operation distribution of code interpreter calls across four multimodal models. Tool usages are automatically categorized into image-editing and analysis-related types. Across models,cropis the most frequent operation, suggesting that many interactions rely on localized visual grounding before further reasoning.",
                "position": 969
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.23166/2602.23166v2/x7.png",
                "caption": "Figure 7:Tool ablation onGemini-3-ProandClaude-Sonnet-4.5. Both models perform best with the full tool suite, highlighting the importance of combining visual manipulation and retrieval.",
                "position": 986
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.23166/2602.23166v2/x8.png",
                "caption": "Figure 8:Error category distribution onAgentVistaacross four multimodal models. Error types are automatically labeled byGemini-3-Flashbased on model trajectories. Across all models,visual misidentificationis the dominant failure mode, indicating that many errors originate from incorrect grounding on fine-grained visual evidence.",
                "position": 996
            }
